<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1245,2026]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,555,1497,1522]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">
Comments on 
<typeStatus box="[382,433,1497,1522]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">type</typeStatus>
material.
</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[623,721,1497,1522]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">holotype</typeStatus>
is glued together and in poor condition. Presumably it was dissected for illustrations of mouthparts in the original publication (
<figureCitation box="[904,986,1533,1558]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1823,1846]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,279,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,265,1800]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Type specimens of Platysodes. 1 – 5. Male holotype of Platysodes formosanus Kobayashi, 1990: 1. dorsal; 2. ventral; 3. lateral; 4. parameres; 5. labels. 6 – 10. Male holotype of Platysodes jansoni Arrow, 1910: 6. dorsal; 7. ventral; 8. lateral; 9. parameres; 10. labels. 11 – 13. Female holotype of Platysodes verlorenii Westwood, 1873: 11. dorsal; 12. labels; 13. dorsal and mouthpart illustrations in original publication (after Westwood 1837)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240956/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">
Fig. 
<number box="[955,986,1534,1558]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). There are two words in the label of the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,1570,1594]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">type</typeStatus>
specimen, “Blume” and “Java”. “Blume” probably refers to Carl Ludwig Blume (
<date box="[1160,1291,1569,1594]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" value="1796" valueMax="1862">
<number box="[1160,1291,1569,1594]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" value="1829.0" valueMax="1862.0" valueMin="1796.0">1796–1862</number>
</date>
), a German- Dutch botanist and entomologist who collected enormous amounts of specimens in the 
<collectingCountry box="[1170,1375,1605,1630]" name="Indonesia" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Dutch East Indies</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis box="[1395,1429,1606,1629]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">i.e.</emphasis>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,262,1641,1666]" name="Indonesia" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
) and worked at Leiden (
<bibRefCitation author="Bartelds" box="[534,696,1641,1666]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" refString="Bartelds, J. C. E. (1930) Blume (Dr. Carl Ludwig). In: Molhuysen, P. C., Blok, P. J. &amp; Kossmann, K. H. (Eds.), Nieuw Nederlandsch Biografisch Woordenboek. Vol. 8. Sijthoff, Leiden, pp. 132 - 133." type="book" year="1930">
Bartelds 
<number box="[636,696,1642,1666]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" value="1930.0">1930</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
