<date box="[823,928,1714,1738]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" value="1992-07">
VII. 
<number box="[869,928,1714,1738]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</date>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="562" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1245,2026]" box="[199,907,1749,1774]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1749,1774]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,468,1749,1774]" name="Indonesia" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(Java, Kalimantan); 
<collectingCountry box="[703,806,1749,1774]" name="Malaysia" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(Sabah).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1245,2026]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,375,1785,1810]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Nomenclature.</emphasis>
According to the original publication (
<bibRefCitation author="Westwood" box="[822,1009,1785,1810]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" refString="Westwood, J. O. (1873) Thesaurus Entomologicus Oxoniensis; or, Illustrations of new, rare, and interesting insects, for the most part contained in the collections presented to the University of Oxford by the Rev. F. W. Hope. Clarendon Press, Oxford, 56 pp., 10 pls. (part 1)." type="book" year="1873">
Westwood 
<number box="[950,1009,1786,1810]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" value="1873.0">1873</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), the use of the genitive ending - 
<emphasis box="[1388,1404,1786,1809]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">ii</emphasis>
of the species name of this species is based upon a personal name, so the correct original spelling, 
<taxonomicName box="[1237,1346,1821,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Platysodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verlorenii">
<emphasis box="[1237,1346,1821,1846]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">verlorenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, should be preserved as the Articles 31.1 and 33.4 (International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature 
<number box="[1264,1324,1858,1882]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" value="1999.0">1999</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="563" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1245,2026]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="563" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1893,1918]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[326,567,1893,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Platysodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verlorenii">
<emphasis box="[326,567,1893,1918]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Platysodes verlorenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the species in the genus with the most southerly distribution. No male specimen have been discovered to date. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai" box="[606,873,1929,1954]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" refString="Sakai, K. &amp; Nagai, S. (1998) The Cetoniine Beetles of the World. Mushi-Sha's Iconographic Series of Insects. Vol. 3. Mushi- Sha, Tokyo, 421 pp." type="book" year="1998">
Sakai and Nagai (
<number box="[807,865,1930,1954]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[929,1331,1929,1954]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" refString="Legrand, J. - P. &amp; Chew Kea Foo, S. (2010) Les Cetoniinae du Sabah. Edition Magellanes. Collection Ex Natura, 1, 1 - 125." type="journal article">
Legrand and Chew Kea Foo (
<number box="[1264,1323,1930,1954]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded two females from Borneo with a white macula behind the humeral umbone, although this maculae is not present in the female 
<typeStatus box="[280,382,2001,2026]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">holotype</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[394,803,2001,2026]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" refString="Legrand, J. - P. &amp; Chew Kea Foo, S. (2010) Les Cetoniinae du Sabah. Edition Magellanes. Collection Ex Natura, 1, 1 - 125." type="journal article">
Legrand and Chew Kea Foo (
<number box="[736,795,2002,2026]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that the elytral distal declivities bear a matte area, that can also be seen in the illustrations of the original publication (
<bibRefCitation author="Westwood" box="[977,1165,151,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563" refString="Westwood, J. O. (1873) Thesaurus Entomologicus Oxoniensis; or, Illustrations of new, rare, and interesting insects, for the most part contained in the collections presented to the University of Oxford by the Rev. F. W. Hope. Clarendon Press, Oxford, 56 pp., 10 pls. (part 1)." type="book" year="1873">
Westwood 
<number box="[1105,1165,152,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="563" value="1873.0">1873</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is a character not present in other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
